CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 12, 1958, pg. A12 reads: "Well Dressed - Winning cups for being among Pittsburgh's well-dressed women at the D.I.'s Easter Sunday affair at the New Nixon, were these charmers. Left to right: Pauline Stotts, Gladys Robinson, Phyllis Pitts, Jayne Moore, Catherine Greene, Sue Corsey and Birdie Dunlap.  Left, rear, Johnny Johnson who presented loving cups to the seven fetching matrons. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven D.I. members, from left: Gloria Golden Grate, Nellye Barron, Gay DeHall, Juanita Drake, Elayne Jones, Ruby Young Buchanan, and Margaret Watson, standing in interior of the New Nixon for the D.I.'s "Breath of Spring" revue
